    <stitle>2 SPEED AXLE SHIFT UNIT: EATON - ELECTRIC SHIFT UNIT - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="8">
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove Slider Block</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To remove the slider block, it is necessary to separate the base housing from the motor
                        housing (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1400202">Figure 2</hotlnk>). Gasket compound may cause these housings to stick
                        together. Use the motor as a handle to assist in separating the housings. If necessary,
                        carefully pry housings apart with a thin-blade screwdriver.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1400202" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400202" filename="../figg14/g1400202.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Slider Block Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the capscrews fastening the base housing to the motor housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the motor housing off the base housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift out slider block and shaft assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400203">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400203" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400203" filename="../figg14/g1400203.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. Slider Block and Shaft Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove Circuit Board and Motor</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the capscrews fastening the cover to the motor housing.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Gasket compound may cause the cover to stick to the housing. If necessary, carefully pry
                            it loose with a thin-blade screwdriver.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect lead wires at cover terminals (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400204">Figure 4</hotlnk>). Remove cover. Remove circuit board locknut.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400204" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400204" filename="../figg14/g1400204.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4. Lead Wire Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift circuit board out to gain access to the motor lead wire (black) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400205">Figure 5</hotlnk>). Disconnect this wire, then remove the circuit board.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400205" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400205" filename="../figg14/g1400205.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5. Circuit Board Removal</caption>
                </figure>
                <para></para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove circuit board mounting washer (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400206">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400206" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400206" filename="../figg14/g1400206.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6. Circuit Board Mounting Washer Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the capscrews fastening the motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the motor to separate it from the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400207">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400207" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400207" filename="../figg14/g1400207.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7. Motor Removal</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Gasket compound may cause the motor to stick to the housing. If necessary, separate the
                            motor from the housing by carefully prying with a thin-blade screwdriver.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the motor, carefully guiding the motor wire and terminal through the housing
                    hole.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove Gear and Cam Pins</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the gear locknut with a deep well socket while holding shaft end with locking
                    pliers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400208">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400208" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400208" filename="../figg14/g1400208.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8. Gear Locknut Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the ground lead wire.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift shaft and gear assembly out of housing.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The cam pins are removed from the gear side of the housing. Do not disturb the switch
                            spring.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cam pins from the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400209">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400209" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400209" filename="../figg14/g1400209.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9. Cam Pin Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
